                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> It depends on the type of player you are.<br /><br />If you solo, this doesn't do a whole lot of good, unless you want to start throwing out Cripling Claudication while soloing.  To me the benefit you would get with this doesn't justify the AA.<br /><br />Non-LDoN grouping.  Would be very beneficial for group situations.  <br /><br />LDoN Grouping - Unless you can get your group to buff inside, which isn't the best idea because of the timelimit, it's worthless.  I know, you should never need all the time in normal adv's, but stuff happens.  People go LD, a really bad pull causes multiple deaths, etc..<br /><br />Raiding - Nice boost here.  It will let your pet stay alive much longer because of all the resists he will get (goD, bard Song) and the HP buffs (focus, boar, Pot9/kazzad).  The only problem here is that pets aren't allowed on all raids.<br /><br />So, my take is if you primarily solo or do LDON adv, then this isn't worth your while.  But if you group and raid a lot, it may be a worthwhile investment.<br /><br />What I would like to see for Ldon, is a buffing room.  Where you zone in, but are in a room with 4 walls and an NPC.  Then do the hedge quest type of insta port when the group leader says "we are ready".  The adv timer doesn't start until the GL says this and the 30 minute countdown to start the adventure doesn't stop until you say that.</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
